%N A396314 Numbers k > 1 for which A396316(k) is not the greatest prime factor of k.
%C A396314 Write the greatest prime factor of an integer m as gpf(m) = A006530(m) and the abundancy of m as abun(m) = sigma(m)/m, where sigma is the sum of divisors function. All integers m > 1 have a proper divisor, d, for which abun(d) >= abun(m) * gpf(m)/(gpf(m)+1). These are the numbers, k, for which the inequality is strict.
%C A396314 All terms are nonsquarefree (see A013929). They include all numbers k whose largest prime power divisor, A034699(k), is larger than gpf(k), but also others (starting with 20, 60, 88, 99, 104, 198).
%Y A396314 Cf. A000203 (sigma), A006530, A017665/A017666 (abundancy), A034699, A396316.
%Y A396314 Subsequence of A013929.
%Y A396314 A122145 is a subsequence.
%K A396314 nonn,new
%O A396314 1,1
